256
00:23:47,911 --> 00:23:49,952
You be careful.

257
00:23:49,987 --> 00:23:53,453
Lot of folks losin' their jobs.
Christmas next week.

258
00:23:54,669 --> 00:23:56,136
Yeah.

259
00:23:56,685 --> 00:24:00,523
Mrs. Thompson ain't as bad as some.
She called that policeman out for me.

260
00:24:00,558 --> 00:24:03,386
I ain't never seen a white woman
do nothin' like that before.

261
00:24:03,421 --> 00:24:06,858
Odessa, don't you go foolin'
yourself 'bout that white woman.

262
00:24:06,893 --> 00:24:10,044
She don't know us,
and she don't want to know us.

263
00:24:10,079 --> 00:24:13,453
She may have a heart of gold, but she
the one that sent you to that park,

264
00:24:13,488 --> 00:24:15,421
and you ain't have
no say in it.

265
00:24:15,456 --> 00:24:18,210
That policeman was
apologizing to her, not you.

266
00:24:18,245 --> 00:24:20,681
Well, still and all,

267
00:24:20,683 --> 00:24:25,631
I cannot keep comin' home too tired to do
the cookin' and too late to do the cleanin'.

268
00:24:35,130 --> 00:24:38,331
- You can always take the bus.
- What?

269
00:24:39,175 --> 00:24:41,077
What did you say?

270
00:24:47,613 --> 00:24:49,247
I guess it's like
the preachers say,

271
00:24:49,249 --> 00:24:51,816
"There's an easy answer
for everything. "

272
00:24:51,818 --> 00:24:54,338
Nobody said it
was gonna be easy.

273
00:25:01,862 --> 00:25:05,197
Mary Catherine, will you stop messing with
that silverware and sit down in that seat.

274
00:25:05,199 --> 00:25:06,967
I'm just playing.

275
00:25:08,737 --> 00:25:11,237
I'm sorry I yelled at you.
Odessa's got a lot of work to do.

276
00:25:11,239 --> 00:25:13,809
Odessa, I'm going to Junior League,
so you'll have Mary Catherine.

277
00:25:13,811 --> 00:25:16,677
- Yes, ma'am.
- Is that all the silver you've done?

278
00:25:18,047 --> 00:25:20,215
I've been feeling
a little poorly today.

279
00:25:23,152 --> 00:25:26,974
Well, you've been feeling poorly all week,
and next week is Christmas.

280
00:25:27,271 --> 00:25:28,641
Yes, ma'am.

281
00:25:31,194 --> 00:25:35,298
Now, I know you can't ride the bus,
and I'm not a taxi service,

282
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:39,270
but I can't have you come in here in the
mornin' and draggin' around all day, Odessa.

283
00:25:39,272 --> 00:25:42,039
Not this close to Christmas.

284
00:25:42,041 --> 00:25:44,743
I go to Curb Market early
on Tuesdays and Fridays,

285
00:25:44,745 --> 00:25:47,344
so I can pick you up between 7:30
and 8:00 on those mornings.

286
00:25:47,346 --> 00:25:49,144
Until you can start
riding the bus.

287
00:25:49,282 --> 00:25:51,905
The other days, you're gonna
have to get here on your own.

288
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:53,220
Mary Catherine?

289
00:26:01,756 --> 00:26:03,239
Mary Catherine!

290
00:26:03,432 --> 00:26:07,067
I don't want you to go tellin' Daddy
I've been carrying Odessa to work.

291
00:26:07,069 --> 00:26:09,237
Now, I've got a good
reason for this, okay?

292
00:26:09,628 --> 00:26:11,404
- Yes, ma'am.
- No slips.

293
00:26:11,439 --> 00:26:13,332
Santa might
get unhappy.

294
00:26:13,367 --> 00:26:14,910
Understood?

295
00:26:14,945 --> 00:26:17,141
Okay.
Bye-bye.

296
00:26:21,951 --> 00:26:25,693
Of course, what I cared about that
Christmas were the little things...

297
00:26:26,223 --> 00:26:31,360
the presents I'd asked for and the way I
thought my older sister owned the world.

298
00:26:33,772 --> 00:26:35,339
Mommy, Mommy!

299
00:26:35,374 --> 00:26:37,797
- They're here! They're here!
- Oh!

300
00:26:38,171 --> 00:26:39,905
- Hi, honey!
- Hi, Mom.

301
00:26:39,907 --> 00:26:42,207
Father says you never
wrote a Christmas list.

302
00:26:42,209 --> 00:26:44,943
- I did mine a month ago.
- Jeepers, Boo-Boo.

303
00:26:44,945 --> 00:26:47,179
- I'm not Boo-Boo.
- Yes, you are, Boo-Boo.

304
00:26:47,181 --> 00:26:48,963
Let me get these bags
to Sara's room,

305
00:26:48,997 --> 00:26:50,810
and then I want to take
you all out for a surprise.

306
00:26:50,889 --> 00:26:52,962
- You mean after dinner.
- No, I mean now.

307
00:26:53,097 --> 00:26:54,737
- Honey!
- It'll be a lot of fun, honey.

308
00:26:54,831 --> 00:26:57,730
I know Sara's hungry, and I just made
her favorite, chicken tetrazzini.

309
00:26:57,817 --> 00:26:59,538
- Ew!
- Mother!

310
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:02,784
I stopped eating chicken tetrazzini
when I was nine years old.

311
00:27:04,066 --> 00:27:07,301
Besides, I had my heart set
on eating at The Elite.

312
00:27:07,336 --> 00:27:10,128
- She made me promise at the airport.
- Honey, I've been cooking all day long.

313
00:27:10,325 --> 00:27:13,384
I promise, I will eat cold
chicken tetrazzini all week.

314
00:27:18,181 --> 00:27:20,521
This is the...
the new subdivision.

315
00:27:20,556 --> 00:27:22,787
It's... 41 lots.

316
00:27:22,822 --> 00:27:26,317
I wasn't gonna bring you
out here till Christmas, but,

317
00:27:26,352 --> 00:27:29,734
they put up these, uh...
these street markers,

318
00:27:29,769 --> 00:27:32,788
and I was just sure that somehow
you were gonna find out. Look.

319
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:36,560
- Is that named after me?
- It sure is.

320
00:27:36,803 --> 00:27:41,088
And, honey, look.
Over there, that's Mary Lane.

321
00:27:41,308 --> 00:27:45,017
And it runs into Catherine Court,
so you have two streets named after you.

322
00:27:45,052 --> 00:27:46,545
- Really? Two streets?
- Yes, indeed.

323
00:27:46,547 --> 00:27:49,960
And way back there,
you can't see it, but...

324
00:27:50,237 --> 00:27:52,086
that's Miriam Street.

325
00:27:52,287 --> 00:27:56,104
So now all the women in my life
have somethin' named after 'em.

326
00:27:56,139 --> 00:27:58,150
And years and years
from now,

327
00:27:58,261 --> 00:28:02,393
you can look back and know that
people lived their lives on your street,

328
00:28:02,428 --> 00:28:04,256
and whenever they said
where they lived,

329
00:28:04,291 --> 00:28:06,176
they used your names.

330
00:28:07,237 --> 00:28:08,830
Merry Christmas.

331
00:28:23,453 --> 00:28:26,719
<i>The air force has spotted an
