00:28:54,428 --> 00:28:56,268
- No.
- Good.

342
00:28:56,303 --> 00:28:59,067
If there was a Santa Claus,
he would have surely swooped down

343
00:28:59,149 --> 00:29:00,932
and replaced that old thing.

344
00:29:00,967 --> 00:29:03,188
Well, I wouldn't hold my breath
waiting for that to happen.

345
00:29:03,223 --> 00:29:06,756
I know.
I'm back in Montgomery again.

346
00:29:06,791 --> 00:29:08,821
Harness the mule.

347
00:29:09,608 --> 00:29:12,986
It's time to go down to the
well and draw some water.

348
00:29:17,765 --> 00:29:20,430
- Miriam.
- Shh. I'm right here.

349
00:29:23,221 --> 00:29:24,655
Shh.

350
00:29:29,996 --> 00:29:33,175
Honey, you're gonna have to
tell me which pile to put these in.

351
00:29:33,210 --> 00:29:35,374
Relax, honey.
It'll be fine.

352
00:29:35,409 --> 00:29:39,438
- I like the layout.
- Well, let's see. Mary Catherine.

353
00:31:03,338 --> 00:31:05,548
Honey. Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas, honey.

354
00:31:05,583 --> 00:31:07,372
Now, wave.
Wave to the camera.

355
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:09,127
Good.

356
00:31:11,594 --> 00:31:14,542
- Okay. Sara?
- Come on.

357
00:31:14,780 --> 00:31:16,901
Merry Christmas, honey.

358
00:31:17,083 --> 00:31:19,684
Sweetness?
Mary Catherine.

359
00:31:19,686 --> 00:31:22,387
Whoo!

360
00:31:23,147 --> 00:31:25,316
- Hold on. Hold on.
- Look at the presents.

361
00:31:25,351 --> 00:31:26,817
Come on, Mary Catherine.

362
00:31:32,048 --> 00:31:34,232
Merry Christmas, Odessa.

363
00:31:35,036 --> 00:31:38,570
Miriam, the Eighth Army
has arrived.

364
00:31:38,605 --> 00:31:41,803
Good morning, Odessa.
