00:31:54,226 --> 00:31:56,926
And when Claudia gets here,
one of you will have to vacuum.

370
00:31:56,961 --> 00:31:59,636
Now, don't forget to
put out the milk punch.

371
00:31:59,671 --> 00:32:01,742
Last year, we were
halfway through the day,

372
00:32:01,777 --> 00:32:03,959
and nobody thought to
put out the milk punch.

373
00:32:03,994 --> 00:32:05,988
Oh, I know I must be
forgettin' somethin'.

374
00:32:06,023 --> 00:32:07,965
Oh!
Merry Christmas, Odessa.

375
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:11,615
- Merry Christmas, Mrs. Thompson. - Mother!
Do I have to wear this stupid dress?

376
00:32:11,848 --> 00:32:15,638
Sara, I ordered these dresses specially
for all of us. Now, they're cute.

377
00:32:15,673 --> 00:32:17,148
Mother!

378
00:32:18,718 --> 00:32:21,587
Dessie, look what I got.
Isn't she pretty?

379
00:32:21,589 --> 00:32:24,723
She's got three whole outfits,
with shoes and socks and everything!

380
00:32:24,725 --> 00:32:28,168
- Three whole outfits!
- Look at her bonnet and her dress

381
00:32:28,203 --> 00:32:30,547
- and the ribbons and the shoes!
- Oh, she's beautiful!

382
00:32:30,582 --> 00:32:31,875
Oh!

383
00:32:31,910 --> 00:32:34,339
Wait until you see
what else I got.

384
00:32:38,140 --> 00:32:40,342
He come runnin' down the stairs,
be so excited,

385
00:32:40,344 --> 00:32:43,711
he'd fly right on right on
and hit his grand keister.

386
00:32:43,713 --> 00:32:45,647
Land on the road.

387
00:32:45,649 --> 00:32:47,715
Does he still do that?

388
00:32:49,519 --> 00:32:52,321
Now let's see if Tunker wants
some of these limas.

389
00:32:52,323 --> 00:32:55,390
Hey, did you see that thing
in the paper this morning?

390
00:32:55,392 --> 00:32:59,643
- I think Grover Hall has lost his mind.
- What are you talking about? What thing?

391
00:32:59,678 --> 00:33:02,010
Didn't you read the paper
this morning, Norman?

392
00:33:02,045 --> 00:33:05,235
He's talking about the ad that Grover
let the coloreds put in the paper,

393
00:33:05,270 --> 00:33:07,473
demanding that we
give in to them.

394
00:33:07,508 --> 00:33:09,263
Well, it's stupid.

395
00:33:09,298 --> 00:33:11,937
It's about one of the stupidest things
that ever happened to this city,

396
00:33:11,972 --> 00:33:14,338
because who really cares
about the buses?

397
00:33:14,898 --> 00:33:17,131
Ah, you don't understand.

398
00:33:17,522 --> 00:33:19,472
This is just a test.

399
00:33:20,178 --> 00:33:24,379
In the paper this morning, they said
they want all the bus drivers' jobs.

400
00:33:24,768 --> 00:33:28,752
- Wouldn't that be great.
- No. It seems to me...

401
00:33:28,787 --> 00:33:31,184
that the way to handle this
thing is to play it down.

402
00:33:31,219 --> 00:33:34,320
Supreme court's just itching
to force this whole issue.

403
00:33:35,079 --> 00:33:37,233
Let 'em sit where they want.

404
00:33:37,535 --> 00:33:39,687
It just won't work that way.

405
00:33:39,722 --> 00:33:43,232
I, for one, won't stand for the niggers
in Montgomery running around

406
00:33:43,299 --> 00:33:45,166
yappin' about how they won.

407
00:33:45,201 --> 00:33:47,158
And don't you think it's
gonna have consequences.

408
00:33:47,185 --> 00:33:50,959
Norman, don't you understand?
If they get by with this bus thing now,

409
00:33:50,994 --> 00:33:54,470
in a few years you won't even be
able to have this Christmas dinner...

410
00:33:54,505 --> 00:33:57,851
'cause you'll have to have the
maids sittin' right beside you.

411
00:33:58,267 --> 00:34:01,922
It's Communism is what it is. Just a
bunch of Communists. All of 'em.

412
00:34:02,402 --> 00:34:04,574
None of 'em are from
Montgomery either.

413
00:34:04,609 --> 00:34:08,278
That Martin Luther King...
He hasn't even lived here a year.

414
00:34:08,375 --> 00:34:13,236
These niggers just want too much,
and they're not willing to work for it.

415
00:34:14,170 --> 00:34:16,492
- Rolls, Mrs. Thompson?
- No, thank you.

416
00:34:18,885 --> 00:34:21,720
Well, that's the way I feel.

417
00:34:22,423 --> 00:34:24,376
I don't care who hears me.

418
00:34:32,568 --> 00:34:35,473
- Thank you, Odessa.
- Thanks, Dessie.

419
00:34:37,007 --> 00:34:38,607
Thank you.

420
00:34:48,885 --> 00:34:53,583
Claudia. Claudia, Odessa.
That was a magnificent meal. It was.

421
00:34:53,701 --> 00:34:56,172
- Here's a little something for you.
Merry Christmas. - Thank you.

422
00:34:56,207 --> 00:34:58,133
Merry Christmas, Odessa.

423
00:34:58,896 --> 00:35:00,838
We, uh...

424
00:35:01,367 --> 00:35:03,935
We were just talkin'
about the bus boycott.

425
00:35:04,294 --> 00:35:07,826
- Claudia, I know, I know you get a
ride with your husband. - Yes, sir.

426
00:35:08,302 --> 00:35:11,045
But, Odessa, you're here
five days a week.

427
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:12,949
How do you get to work?

428
00:35:15,610 --> 00:35:19,936
- Today I walked.
- I mean, on a normal day.

429
00:35:21,689 --> 00:35:26,379
Well, I can't take the bus,
Mr. Thompson, so I... I just...

430
00:35:27,423 --> 00:35:30,391
will find me a ride
where I can.

431
00:35:32,568 --> 00:35:35,312
But if it were safe
to ride the bus...

432
00:35:35,347 --> 00:35:37,738
you'd still rather walk
than sit in the back?

433
00:35:39,342 --> 00:35:42,201
Yes, sir, I would
have to say I would.

434
00:35:43,379 --> 00:35:45,393
That's a long walk.

435
00:35:46,695 --> 00:35:49,741
Yes, sir.
Mighty long.

436
00:35:53,453 --> 00:35:56,238
That was...
It was a delicious meal.

437
00:35:56,462 --> 00:36:00,451
- It really was. Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas, Mr. Thompson.

438
00:36:07,642 --> 00:36:09,442
Well?

439
00:36:10,330 --> 00:36:12,022
Well...

440
00:36:14,294 --> 00:36:16,398
I see your point...

441
00:36:16,658 --> 00:36:20,698
- but I can't blame her because I don't
think she's a problem. - The hell she's not.

442
00:36:20,790 --> 00:36:23,212
Why don't you get a new maid,
get a white maid?

443
00:36:23,247 --> 00:36:27,026
- Mother, she's been with us for
nine years. - She's a problem.

444
00:36:27,364 --> 00:36:32,033
She's not uppity like some.
Not to your face.

445
00:36:32,771 --> 00:36:37,091
But slowly, they all start
asking for more, doing less.

446
00:36:38,143 --> 00:36:39,591
Norm?

447
00:36:41,336 --> 00:36:44,601
You got a good family,
good community here.

448
00:36:45,190 --> 00:36:47,931
When was the last time you
locked your door at night?

449
00:36:48,689 --> 00:36:50,211
Never.

450
00:36:51,306 --> 00:36:53,391
If you give in...

451
00:36:53,666 --> 00:36:56,179
what do you think is gonna
happen to this city?

452
00:36:59,289 --> 00:37:02,227
What do you think is gonna
happen to your family?

453
00:37:03,569 --> 00:37:06,605
No, you gotta hold the line.
We all do.

454
00:37:09,625 --> 00:37:11,625
And if she'd rather walk...

455
