this group or the Klan.

678
00:56:18,725 --> 00:56:21,323
Oh, honey.
That's not true.

679
00:56:21,702 --> 00:56:23,727
The mayor and the commission
are politicians.

680
00:56:23,741 --> 00:56:26,660
They'd join the circus if they
thought it'd get 'em reelected.

681
00:56:26,695 --> 00:56:30,269
You're beginnin' to let your little
brother lead you around by the nose.

682
00:56:30,394 --> 00:56:33,827
Listen, I don't care whether you like Tunker
or not, but don't you tell me what to do.

683
00:56:34,765 --> 00:56:38,629
I'll make up my own mind, and I'll join
any goddamn group I please.

684
00:56:41,822 --> 00:56:44,016
- Are you ready?
- Sure.

685
00:56:55,305 --> 00:56:58,348
- Well, this is not at all what
I expected. - Yeah.

686
00:57:01,302 --> 00:57:05,168
See. No white sheets.
No secret oaths.

687
00:57:05,203 --> 00:57:07,538
You mean I don't get to
learn a coded handshake?

688
00:57:07,571 --> 00:57:10,604
- Is that what you're tryin' to tell me?
- Norm Thompson. - Yeah.

689
00:57:10,639 --> 00:57:13,184
Oh, hi. Jeff Sewell with
Avalon Brothers here in town.

690
00:57:13,186 --> 00:57:15,025
- Oh, right. Nice to see ya.
- Glad you could be out tonight.

691
00:57:15,027 --> 00:57:18,462
- Thank you. - By the way, I've just
been put on the planning commission.

692
00:57:18,464 --> 00:57:21,198
- Uh-huh. - If you ever have a
zoning problem, you give me a ring.

693
00:57:21,200 --> 00:57:23,434
- I can put you right.
- Thanks, Jeff.

694
00:57:25,114 --> 00:57:28,900
Over half the small business owners
in town are members of the council.

695
00:57:29,532 --> 00:57:31,731
You mean half the white
small businesses.

696
00:57:31,846 --> 00:57:35,063
If you call what the niggers do business,
Commissioner Sellers.

697
00:57:35,326 --> 00:57:37,514
- How you doing, Clyde?
- Holdin' on.

698
00:57:37,791 --> 00:57:39,594
Didn't think you'd be
out here after that

699
00:57:39,629 --> 00:57:42,023
phone call I got from
your wife a while back.

700
00:57:42,747 --> 00:57:46,564
She was right though. The police
department's gotta keep its nose clean.

701
00:57:46,919 --> 00:57:50,251
Hope you can get the rest of that country
club crowd to some of these meetings.

702
00:57:50,378 --> 00:57:51,892
If the niggers keep pushin'
the way they are,

703
00:57:52,085 --> 00:57:55,095
- we'll get 'em off the golf
courses for ya. - No, no.

704
00:57:56,139 --> 00:57:58,140
What I want is to get
'em on the course.

705
00:57:59,099 --> 00:58:02,546
Best caddy I ever had
was a nigger.

706
00:58:07,350 --> 00:58:10,473
Testing.
One, two, three.

707
00:58:11,490 --> 00:58:15,359
Testing.
One, two, three.

708
00:58:15,361 --> 00:58:21,024
- I know the journey... has been hard.
- Yes. Yeah.

709
00:58:22,368 --> 00:58:26,118
- Many of you are tired.
- Right. Yeah.

710
00:58:26,153 --> 00:58:29,068
- Still tired.
- We've seen the city,

711
00:58:29,577 --> 00:58:34,098
and it's turned its back
on its black children.

712
00:58:36,825 --> 00:58:41,051
We've seen the mayor
and city commission,

713
00:58:42,031 --> 00:58:44,918
which has taken a stand...

714
00:58:45,545 --> 00:58:49,335
- for injustice...
- Yes. Amen.

715
00:58:49,433 --> 00:58:51,656
- and bigotry.
- Yes.

716
00:58:52,069 --> 00:58:56,072
- Moses.
- Moses.

717
00:58:56,074 --> 00:58:59,343
- Moses!
- Yes. Moses.

718
00:58:59,345 --> 00:59:04,647
- Fought the pharaoh long
and hard for his people. - Yes.

719
00:59:06,544 --> 00:59:10,399
- What? Oh!
- But Moses stood tall for his people.

720
00:59:10,689 --> 00:59:12,930
Tall, yeah.

721
00:59:13,704 --> 00:59:16,491
When the children of Israel...

722
00:59:16,791 --> 00:59:19,998
were led out
into the wilderness,

723
00:59:20,710 --> 00:59:25,303
- they didn't walk for just
one month or two. - No.

724
00:59:25,907 --> 00:59:30,472
- They walked for 40 long years.
- All right. All right.

725
00:59:32,195 --> 00:59:35,404
They just bombed
Reverend King's house.

726
00:59:47,664 --> 00:59:48,964
Wait.

727
00:59:51,335 --> 00:59:54,102
Let us pray.

728
00:59:54,104 --> 00:59:57,903
- Father, I've just heard
terrible news. - Yeah.

729
00:59:59,100 --> 01:00:02,829
I've heard that a bomb
was thrown at the house...

730
01:00:03,035 --> 01:00:06,442
of a young man
so full of spirit.

731
01:00:07,686 --> 01:00:10,722
Father, we pray...

732
01:00:11,020 --> 01:00:16,885
- in thanks, for sparing the life of
Reverend Martin Luther King Jr. - Yes!

733
01:00:21,403 --> 01:00:24,626
- Lord, be by our side.
- Yeah.

734
01:00:25,005 --> 01:00:30,158
These dark days... hold our hand
as we walk through the night.

735
01:00:30,429 --> 01:00:31,837
- Yeah.
- Yes.

736
01:00:31,872 --> 01:00:35,609
- Lord, don't pass Montgomery by!
- Yes.

737
01:00:38,759 --> 01:00:42,393
- Don't pass Montgomery by tonight.
- Yeah.

738
01:03:10,358 --> 01:03:12,626
Oh.

739
01:03:32,967 --> 01:03:36,266
- Is there anything you need, honey?
- No, no.

740
01:03:36,757 --> 01:03:38,611
When's Odessa gettin' here?

741
01:03:38,646 --> 01:03:41,925
Well, she's probably gonna be a
little late on account of the rain.

742
01:03:42,459 --> 01:03:44,916
Isn't she usually
here by now?

743
01:03:45,364 --> 01:03:47,118
Not really.

744
01:03:48,432 --> 01:03:50,989
You mean she
comes in late a lot?

745
01:03:52,470 --> 01:03:56,717
Odessa gets here just fine every day.
Now, I've got to go.

746
01:03:57,376 --> 01:03:59,270
She'll be here soon enough.

747
01:03:59,580 --> 01:04:01,005
Miriam.

748
01:04:02,144 --> 01:04:03,961
Yeah.

749
01:04:05,662 --> 01:04:08,206
Just how does Odessa
get to work?

750
01:04:11,700 --> 01:04:15,170
Well, I was goin' over to
the Curb Market today anyway,

751
01:04:15,281 --> 01:04:17,878
and that's over on Madison
near where Odessa lives,

752
01:04:18,162 --> 01:04:22,181
- and I was just gonna go ahead and
pick her up. - You're gonna do what?

753
01:04:22,561 --> 01:04:25,218
How often do you
drive her around?

754
01:04:27,594 --> 01:04:30,169
Well, I go to Curb Market
twice a week.

755
01:04:31,550 --> 01:04:34,604
- That's it. - Here I am tryin'
to hold my head up as a

756
01:04:34,837 --> 01:04:37,633
white man in this town,
and you're cartin' a nigger maid.

757
01:04:37,648 --> 01:04:41,148
No wonder none of 'em are ridin' the buses.
They have you to carry 'em around.

758
01:04:43,427 --> 01:04:44,962
What should I do?

759
01:04:44,964 --> 01:04:47,999
Odessa walks to work three days
a week. She can walk five.

760
01:04:48,001 --> 01:04:50,568
You can just get on the
phone and call her now.

761
01:04:50,570 --> 01:04:52,937
- Norman.
- Now, damn it!

762
01:05:08,722 --> 01:05:10,557
Hello.

763
01:05:13,964 --> 01:05:17,979
Yes, ma'am, I can be to work.
I'll just be a little late.

764
01:05:55,491 --> 01:05:57,462
- Oh.
- Miriam?

765
01:05:57,799 --> 01:05:59,840
Damn.

766
01:06:08,786 --> 01:06:11,611
I'm sorry I got
so upset before.

767
01:06:12,508 --> 01:06:15,252
- Can I talk to you for a minute?
- Yeah.

768
01:06:30,060 --> 01:06:32,668
I know you don't
keep up with things.

769
01:06:33,988 --> 01:06:37,694
Even I thought this boycott business
was silly when it first started.

770
01:06:38,029 --> 01:06:40,388
And if it wasn't
being made into...

771
01:06:40,464 --> 01:06:45,105
such a circus by the coloreds,
I'd still think it was silly. But...

772
01:06:45,824 --> 01:06:47,848
...it's not anymore.

773
01:06:49,648 --> 01:06:52,256
And drivin' Odessa
to work, it...

774
01:06:52,928 --> 01:06:56,319
just wasn't the right thing to do.
You know that.

775
01:06:59,356 --> 01:07:04,050
I think Odessa... has been
a wonderful maid for us,

776
01:07:04,091 --> 01:07:06,965
and when she's here,
that's what she is: A Maid.

777
01:07:07,501 --> 01:07:11,901
And that's not the real Odessa. We don't
know that woman. Can't ever know her.

778
01:07:12,014 --> 01:07:16,860
It's like... a dog knowin' a cat.
It's a different species.

779
01:07:17,010 --> 01:07:20,376
And you drivin' her to work is
tellin' her that she's just like us.

780
01:07:20,423 --> 01:07:22,910
And she's not,
and she never can be.

781
01:07:25,089 --> 01:07:28,568
Even if I thought you didn't
understand that, and I know you do,

782
01:07:28,668 --> 01:07:31,652
I still couldn't let you
drive her to work.

783
01:07:32,050 --> 01:07:36,151
Do you know what would happen to you...
if the wrong people saw you?

784
01:07:36,628 --> 01:07:40,615
You saw the pictures from Tuscaloosa
when they kicked that niggra out.

785
01:07:41,533 --> 01:07:46,876
There are people here, now,
that are ready to do those things.

786
01:07:48,659 --> 01:07:51,011
Don't go off on your own.

787
01:07:52,431 --> 01:07:54,782
You ask me.

788
01:07:55,640 --> 01:07:58,550
I know what's best.

789
01:08:38,198 --> 01:08:39,973
Mrs. Thompson?

790
01:08:44,365 --> 01:08:48,197
- Mrs. Thompson?
- Odessa. I didn't know if you'd make it.

791
01:08:48,412 --> 01:08:50,799
I did the breakfast dishes.

792
01:08:52,515 --> 01:08:55,937
Mrs. Thompson...
why did you call me at home,

793
01:08:56,084 --> 01:08:58,955
and tell me you couldn't carry
me to work anymore?

794
01:09:01,618 --> 01:09:03,963
Well, if...
If you won't ride the bus,

795
01:09:04,154 --> 01:09:07,164
Mr. Thompson doesn't see
why I should have to suffer.

796
01:09:07,362 --> 01:09:10,005
I ain't asked you to suffer,
Mrs. Thompson.

797
01:09:14,672 --> 01:09:17,832
It wasn't me, Odessa.
It was Mr. Thompson.

798
01:09:18,232 --> 01:09:21,226
He was home with a cold today,
and he found out.

799
01:09:23,802 --> 01:09:25,876
Let me get you somethin' dry.

800
01:09:36,595 --> 01:09:38,914
- Here ya are.
- Thank you.

801
01:09:42,379 --> 01:09:45,035
So, what are you gonna do?

802
01:09:47,632 --> 01:09:49,421
I don't know.

803
01:09:49,795 --> 01:09:52,955
I can't walk,
and I can't ride the bus.

804
01:09:53,445 --> 01:09:56,782
Can't you just walk until
this whole mess is over?

805
01:09:59,387 --> 01:10:01,995
Mrs. Thompson,
you a good woman.

806
01:10:04,178 --> 01:10:07,911
But I gotta find me another job.
I gotta quit.

807
01:10:09,118 --> 01:10:11,940
I gotta be able to take
care of my children.

808
01:10:12,608 --> 01:10:16,236
Well, uh, I understand.

809
01:10:17,807 --> 01:10:21,109
You know, it's... It's funny
the way people are.

810
01:10:21,275 --> 01:10:24,416
This mornin' Norman was actin' so sick,
and then he found out I'd been drivin' you,

811
01:10:24,428 --> 01:10:27,464
and he got so mad,
he jumped out of bed.

812
01:10:28,141 --> 01:10:32,306
I guess that got his blood goin', and he
started feelin' better and went on to work.

813
01:10:37,900 --> 01:10:41,330
Norman's just always been where
everything's segregated. That's...

814
01:10:41,379 --> 01:10:43,866
That's just the way he thinks.

815
01:10:48,025 --> 01:10:51,945
When I was 15, my girls club went
on a bus trip across the country.

816
01:10:52,017 --> 01:10:55,039
It was in the '30s,
but my family had some money, and,

817
01:10:55,074 --> 01:10:57,706
I remember we went
to Portland, Oregon.

818
01:10:58,193 --> 01:11:00,775
It was the middle of the summer,
and it was hot, and,

819
01:11:00,810 --> 01:11:04,514
the bus driver found this public
pool for us. We went swimmin'.

820
01:11:04,849 --> 01:11:09,045
Then these two colored boys came
and got in the water. And let me tell ya,

821
01:11:09,080 --> 01:11:13,237
you've never seen 20 girls get out
of a pool so fast in all your life.

822
01:11:14,595 --> 01:11:17,564
We just...
We just didn't know any better.

823
01:11:18,221 --> 01:11:21,300
But I remember watchin'
those other kids in the water.

824
01:11:21,479 --> 01:11:25,020
And they just kept right on swimmin'
with those colored boys, and,

825
01:11:25,067 --> 01:11:27,685
they didn't seem any
the worse for it.

826
01:11:30,288 --> 01:11:32,784
So the rest of the world
around ya is...

827
01:11:34,000 --> 01:11:37,855
livin' that way, and so you
just don't question it.

828
01:11:42,966 --> 01:11:44,933
Years ago...

829
01:11:45,303 --> 01:11:48,903
I decided I'd live with Norman
for the rest of my life.

830
01:11:49,224 --> 01:11:52,678
And part of that means
livin' the way he lives.

831
01:11:54,918 --> 01:11:58,927
But sometimes...
Sometimes Norman says things.

832
01:11:59,193 --> 01:12:04,260
It makes me wonder if he saw as much of the
world durin' the war as he thought he did.

833
01:12:10,896 --> 01:12:14,723
But he's a good man.
He's a good provider.

834
01:12:15,908 --> 01:12:19,654
In a lot of ways, he's a better
husband than I am a wife.

835
01:12:20,054 --> 01:12:22,439
He's better with the children.
He...

836
01:12:22,474 --> 01:12:26,515
You know, he can say a word and
make 'em smile. I can't do that.

837
01:12:26,614 --> 01:12:29,791
Mrs. Thompson, he can't be
a mother to 'em.

838
01:12:32,029 --> 01:12:33,775
Odessa.

839
01:12:34,354 --> 01:12:36,555
You do the motherin'.

840
01:12:36,873 --> 01:12:39,769
I saw the way you held Mary Catherine
when she had the chicken pox,

841
01:12:39,852 --> 01:12:42,158
and you hadn't even had it.

842
01:12:42,821 --> 01:12:46,059
Mrs. Thompson, anybody
would have done that.

843
01:12:47,912 --> 01:12:49,582
I wonder.

844
01:12:50,910 --> 01:12:53,201
Would I have done that
for your daughter?

845
01:13:01,546 --> 01:13:05,282
Mrs. Thompson, I don't want your
children to grow up scared of mine.

846
01:13:09,497 --> 01:13:12,504
It's just that a lot
of the wives are scared.

847
01:13:14,963 --> 01:13:16,895
I'm a little scared.

848
01:13:17,312 --> 01:13:19,729
We all scared.

849
01:13:20,372 --> 01:13:22,934
But what's scarin' you, Mrs. Thompson?
Who you are?

850
01:13:22,969 --> 01:13:25,610
Or who Mr. Thompson
wants you to be?

851
01:13:59,999 --> 01:14:01,400
- Hi.
- Hi.

852
01:14:01,569 --> 01:14:02,947
- Here.
- Oh, thank you.

853
01:14:03,023 --> 01:14:05,114
- Let me take your coat.
- Thank you.

854
01:14:07,048 --> 01:14:11,371
- How's your cold?
- Oh, I'm miserable. I feel like crap.

855
01:14:11,421 --> 01:14:13,614
Well, that's nice, honey.

856
01:14:13,649 --> 01:14:15,987
Odessa walked to work today.

857
01:14:16,022 --> 01:14:18,949
- Oh, you told her she had to?
- In the rain.

858
01:14:18,984 --> 01:14:20,534
From Cobb Street.

859
01:14:21,174 --> 01:14:23,477
But she's not walking again.

860
01:14:23,479 --> 01:14:25,579
- No?
- No.

861
01:14:25,612 --> 01:14:28,611
You have your job, and I
guess you do it just fine.

862
01:14:28,962 --> 01:14:33,177
My job is to run this house. And as
long as it's clean, supper's cooked,

863
01:14:33,223 --> 01:14:35,951
and the laundry... the laundry
gets done, I don't...

864
01:14:37,342 --> 01:14:40,461
I don't think it's any of your
business how it happens.

865
01:14:40,648 --> 01:14:43,792
Wait a second. Aren't you forgettin'
who pays the bills around here?

866
01:14:43,827 --> 01:14:47,002
Well then, what time should
I be ready tomorrow?

867
01:14:47,394 --> 01:14:48,846
Ready for what?

868
01:14:48,987 --> 01:14:52,213
Well, I'm gonna go downtown with you in
the mornin' and help you with your job.

869
01:14:52,248 --> 01:14:54,590
You seem so intent on
helping me with mine.

870
01:14:54,625 --> 01:14:57,324
Or if you don't like that idea,
I do have a college education,

871
01:14:57,359 --> 01:14:59,692
so I'll just go out and
get a job of my own.

872
01:14:59,727 --> 01:15:02,805
It'll probably be somethin' secretarial,
but I'm sure I'll manage.

873
01:15:02,840 --> 01:15:05,421
You will have to take on a lot of
the housework, which will include

874
01:15:05,495 --> 01:15:07,262
finding a maid who
can get out here.

875
01:15:07,435 --> 01:15:10,613
But the money I earn will be my own,
and I'll do with it what I damn well please.

876
01:15:10,642 --> 01:15:12,818
- You're serious...
- And that includes givin' it all to that

877
01:15:13,064 --> 01:15:15,002
Reverend King and the Montgomery
Improvement Association,

878
01:15:15,103 --> 01:15:17,651
so they can put an end to
this whole boycott mess.

879
01:15:23,969 --> 01:15:27,282
Now, do you really care
if I drive Odessa to work?

880
01:15:34,947 --> 01:15:36,722
We're havin' pork chops
for supper,

881
01:15:36,757 --> 01:15:39,938
and I told Mary Catherine that you'd
read to her before she went to sleep.

882
01:15:52,177 --> 01:15:54,940
Did you get Mary Catherine
to bed?

883
01:15:55,242 --> 01:15:56,923
Yeah.

884
01:16:01,510 --> 01:16:03,655
What are you doin'?

885
01:16:07,229 --> 01:16:09,495
Oh, are you just not
gonna talk to me?

886
01:16:13,364 --> 01:16:16,475
Honey, there's no reason
to be so mad.

887
01:16:22,159 --> 01:16:25,711
- Norman, talk to me.
- You already made up your mind.

888
01:16:25,829 --> 01:16:29,319
- No need to talk to me.
- Honey, I'm doin' what I think is right.

889
01:16:30,319 --> 01:16:32,554
Where are you going?

890
01:16:33,624 --> 01:16:35,911
Norman, I'm still your wife.

891
01:16:38,336 --> 01:16:39,828
Yeah, that's all you are.

892
01:16:57,249 --> 01:16:59,518
Odessa, come on,
sit up front with me.

893
01:17:28,851 --> 01:17:32,691
Odessa, how does that
carpooling system work?

894
01:17:34,558 --> 01:17:36,993
Well, I don't use it often,
Mrs. Thompson,

895
01:17:37,028 --> 01:17:40,804
but I believe that drivers
come at the end of day,

896
01:17:40,839 --> 01:17:44,935
to places like Cloverdale, and they pick
up the women that need the rides.

897
01:17:45,868 --> 01:17:48,733
It's a little more organized
than that, isn't it?

898
01:17:49,666 --> 01:17:53,328
Yes.
Yes, it is.

899
01:17:58,009 --> 01:18:00,389
They look for the ringleaders
of the boycott,

900
01:18:00,528 --> 01:18:02,850
they pull 'em over
and give 'em tickets.

901
01:18:02,875 --> 01:18:06,403
If they see too many coloreds in the car,
they pull them over too.

902
01:18:07,241 --> 01:18:09,176
I'll probably get
lots of tickets.

